PRETORIA, South Africa, November 23, 2018/APO Group/ --
                                                        
                            The Minister in the Presidency Responsible for Women, Minister Bathabile Dlamini, invites members of the media to a joint press briefing to introduce the 2018 events for the 16 Days of Activism Campaign Against Violence on Women and Children. The Minister will be joined by leaders of the women’s movement from across various sectors addressing Gender-Based Violence.



Members of the media are invited as follows:

Date: Saturday, 24 November 2018

Time: 09h00

Venue: GCIS, Tshedimosetso House, Cnr Frances Baard and Festival streets, Hatfield in Pretoria

NB: There will be a video link up to Imbizo Media Centre, 120 Plein Street, Parliament in Cape Town



RSVP: Takalani Mukwevho (Pretoria) on takalanim@gcis.gov.za/ 082 227 9308 and Loedfie Hendricks (Cape Town) on loedfie@gcis.gov.za/ 082 670 4145